 Prompt 4 – First Response Email

## Version 1 (v4.1)

### Prompt
Write a reply to a customer enquiry.

### Change Made
Initial version

### Observed Effect
Basic reply with no personalisation or CTA 
Weak engagement
Not aligned with sales goals

### Lesson Learned
Responses must include structure and purpose


## Version 2 (v4.2)

### Prompt
Imagine yourself as a Flexikitch sales representative. Write a first response email to a café owner enquiry. Include thank you, relevant benefits, and CTA to book consultation. Keep professional and under 150 words.

### Change Made
Added sales representative role, defined structure (thank you, benefits, CTA), added constraints like tone and word limit

### Observed Effect
Consistent, professional responses and higher engagement potential

### Lesson Learned
Structured prompts improve focus on conversion communication
